OL,4,CCovid in Scotland: Drinking at the bar
OL,5,Cwill be allowed in pubs
OL,6, Scotland's national clinical director
OL,7, has confirmed that drinking at the bar
OL,8, will be allowed in pubs from next week.
OL,10,FProf Jason Leitch also indicated that
OL,11,Fpeople dancing at nightclubs would not
OL,12,Fbe required to wear face coverings.
OL,14,FIt follows earlier confusion about so
OL,15,Fcalled "vertical drinking" which has
OL,16,Fnot been permitted during previous
OL,17,Flockdown easing.
OL,19,FThe deputy first minister earlier told
OL,20,Fthe BBC it would remain banned when
OL,21,Fmost restrictions are lifted on Monday.
